ART :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Any tips or anything like that? <p><font color="red"><I><B>Gntik</B><BR>Gnomish Rogue of Tallon Zek<BR><B>Krazik</B><BR>Ogre Shadowknight of Tallon Zek<BR>()</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umadelinetz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Madeline TZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/16/00 7:38:56 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/kaydenjadir/minidolly.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mages?</span><hr size=1> Instill doubt, plenty of pumice, and maybe some root poisons.  I prolly fear mages more then anyone.  Their damage shields are just nasty!  Plus that stupid earth pet manages to drop my sow no matter how blue or green he cons.<br>
<br>
Try to fight in tight quarters and use bugged NPC pathing to your advantage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif width=0 height=0 border=0 BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/16/00 8:34:37 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/trinity.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mages?</span><hr size=1> Outside of pumicing the pet...<br>
<br>
I'm not sure of the level range here, or how much that affects it in the later levels, but since around level 15 I have NEVER had the earth pet root EVER even stick on me. The key is magic resistance, and it's not hard at all to resist the earth elemental root spell. Yes, this is fighting yellow or even red mages (rarely con pets maybe thats my problem).<br>
<br>
Anyway like I said maybe this changes at later levels, but I haven't noticed a change yet. A dwarven tunic, MoD, and BS mantle should be plenty to stop earth pet roots, and normal root won't be too effective against you either.<br>
<br>
(On a side note, level differences constitute a 5 resist difference; ie if someone is one level higher then you, it's like having all your resistances dropped by five...this could be devastating on the team servers I imagine, with as much as 40 changing)<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><a href="maileto:chris.painter@juno.com">Canbik the Rogue</a> (23)<br>
<a href="http://pub21.ezboard.com/bsilentvigilforums">Silent Vigil</a><br>
<a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse">Ring Warden of Rallos Zek</a><br>
"I will make your mother childless..."<br>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/16/00 10:37:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mages?</span><hr size=1> untill you hit.. around level 12.. you really cant stop mage earth pets.<br>
<br>
after that, you dont have much of a problem as long as you can get some MR gear.  <br>
<br>
Think of how often you resist root with good mr, then multiply that by 35, thats how often you resist earth pet roots.<br>
<br>
if the pet roots you, beat on him for a little bit..<br>
when it breaks... run for the caster... stab him a little.... then repeat when needed... eventually you will both be low on health.. he will be out of mana.. the pet will die.. and he will either run, or die..<br>
<br>
i hate mages. especially gnome mages <p><img href="http://www.phata.com" src="http://64.188.8.38/images/cylant.jpg"></img><br>
