</font></center></p> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=blimpifingerslippi>Blimpi Fingerslippi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/00 9:01:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mages?</span><hr size=1>    Well - If you are jumpin' the mage, wait for him to not be looking then pull the pet away where the mage/group won't see you fighting. Beat the @#%$ out of it. Pull with a range weapon btw, that way you are out of range of the root spell. Otherwise, if it's the opposite, at lower levels mage pet's hps suck. Kill it then go for the mage because their nukes ain't too strong. This even worked with my 10 monk vs a 9 mage. Besides that, just crank up the MR. <p><font face="aria" ptsize=8><b>Blimpi Fingerslippi</b><font><br>
<font ptsize=8Tallon-Zek</font></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=blimpifingerslippi>Blimpi Fingerslippi</A> at: 12/17/00 9:15:30 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/00 11:03:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mages?</span><hr size=1> 1. Get your Fire Resistance up and kill or fear the auto-root machine.  Then go after the finger waggler.<br>
<br>
